'use client';

/**
 * @file page.tsx
 * @input Deterministic fixtures only (180 SaaS accounts generated by a
 *   seeded PRNG at module load — spend, engagement, seats, segment, region —
 *   so identical fixtures always produce identical pixels)
 * @output Brushing-and-linking metric lab: a hand-rolled SVG scatter of
 *   monthly spend vs engagement (dot radius maps seats, dot color maps
 *   segment) with a draggable rectangle brush — pointer events with capture,
 *   move/resize via corner handles that grow to ~44px hit targets on touch,
 *   plus a full keyboard path (Enter creates, arrows nudge, Shift+arrows
 *   resize, Escape clears) driving the identical reducer actions — linked
 *   bidirectionally to a 12-bin spend histogram (drag across bins or
 *   click / Shift+click bin buttons to brush a spend range that filters the
 *   scatter back) and a segment bar chart with toggle buttons, all above a
 *   compact brushed-accounts Table. Active selections render as removable
 *   Token chips, and a lasso-stats strip (count, median spend, total seats)
 *   recomputes from the brushed set on every pointer move.
 * @position Page template; emitted by `astryx template metric-brush-explorer`
 *
 * Frame: Layout height="fill". LayoutHeader carries the chrome (title, live
 * "N of 180 brushed" readout, Clear-all Button). LayoutContent scrolls a
 * centered max-w-6xl column: filter-chip strip, lasso-stats Stat row, the
 * three linked chart Cards, then the account Table Card.
 *
 * Container policy: this is an analytics explorable, so each chart is a Card
 * widget and the table lives in its own Card; the page chrome stays
 * frame-first (Layout/LayoutHeader/LayoutContent, no ad hoc shells).
 *
 * Responsive contract:
 * - Page column: maxWidth 1152, centered; the whole content area scrolls.
 * - >640px: charts sit in a 2-column CSS grid — the scatter spans both rows
 *   on the left (3fr), histogram and segment bars stack on the right (2fr).
 * - <=640px: single-pane fallback — the three chart Cards become a
 *   horizontal scroll-snap carousel (each slide 100% wide, snap-start,
 *   deliberate overflowX) with a swipe hint line; the brush stays fully
 *   touch-operable because corner-handle hit zones grow to ~44px and the
 *   whole gesture runs on pointer events with capture, never hover.
 * - Stats row: Grid columns={{minWidth: 180, max: 3}} — 3-up wide, 1-up on
 *   phones. Chip strip wraps. Table scrolls horizontally inside its Card
 *   below ~640px (pixel numeric columns keep digits stable).
 * - Tap targets: segment-toggle rows and histogram bins are >=40px-tall
 *   buttons; preset-brush and clear Buttons are standard >=32px controls
 *   with padded rows; nothing is hover-only (the histogram bin summary uses
 *   a native title on hover pointers but the same numbers always render in
 *   the bin caption line).
 * - Motion: dot dim/undim and bar-width transitions are suppressed when
 *   prefers-reduced-motion is set (state changes still apply instantly).
 *
 * Color policy: token-pure — every color resolves through var(--color-*)
 * tokens or color-mix() over those tokens (translucent brush fills and
 * ghost bars included), so the whole surface re-themes in dark mode with no
 * raw hex/rgb literals anywhere in this file.
 *
 * Fixture policy: fixed seeded data only; no Date.now, no Math.random at
 * render time, no network assets. Every derived number is a pure function
 * of the fixture array and the selection-reducer state.
 */

